# Flashcards System

Flashcards are the memory reinforcement engine of LexMastery.

They power long-term retention.

---

# Product Vision

Flashcards must:

- strengthen memory recall
- use spaced repetition
- adapt to user performance
- reduce forgetting curve
- reinforce weak topics

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

FlashcardsController (Riverpod)

↓

FlashcardsState

↓

FlashcardsRepository

↓

SRS Engine (Spaced Repetition System)

---

# State Management

FlashcardsState includes:

- loading
- reviewing
- answered
- completed
- error

Core Data:

- deck
- currentCard
- easeFactor
- interval
- nextReviewDate
- performanceHistory

---

# Spaced Repetition System

Based on:

- correctness
- response time
- confidence level

Adjust:

- interval
- difficulty
- repetition frequency

---

# Card Types

- Basic Q&A
- Legal concept cards
- Scenario cards
- Definition cards

---

# Review Flow

1. Show question
2. User attempts answer
3. Reveal correct answer
4. User rates difficulty
5. System adjusts schedule

---

# Offline Behaviour

Flashcards must work fully offline.

Sync when online.

---

# API Contracts

GET /flashcards/decks

GET /flashcards/{deckId}

POST /flashcards/review

POST /flashcards/sync

---

# Analytics Events

flashcard_open

flashcard_answer

flashcard_difficulty_rating

flashcard_session_complete

---

# UI Composition Rules

Flashcards UI must include:

- single card focus
- flip animation
- difficulty rating buttons
- progress indicator

---

# UX Rules

- minimal distraction
- fast interaction loop
- focus on recall, not reading

---

# Error Handling

- preserve session state
- retry sync automatically

---

# Performance

- instant card rendering
- prefetch next card

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- screen reader card reading
- keyboard shortcuts
- high contrast mode

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

SRS algorithm

Scheduling logic

Controller state

Widget Tests:

Card UI

Review flow

Rating interaction

Integration Tests:

Full study session

Offline review session

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating flashcards:

- always implement spaced repetition logic
- always support offline mode
- always track performance history
- never treat flashcards as static content